HEADWORD: Sterquilinous
<hw>Ster*quil"i*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sterquilinium</ets> a dung pit, fr. <ets>stercus</ets> dung.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to a dunghill; hence, mean; dirty; paltry.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
